Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Module import errors

Ensure you're running scripts from the scripts/ directory
Verify __init__.py exists in the scripts folder
Check that config path is correctly added to sys.path
Issue: Missing data or empty results

Verify sample data was generated successfully
Check CSV file format matches expected structure
Ensure all required columns are present in survey data
Issue: Visualization errors in headless environment

Confirm matplotlib backend is set to 'Agg'
Check that output directories exist before saving plots
Verify sufficient permissions to write to reports directory
Issue: Incorrect maturity level calculations

Review scoring thresholds in configuration
Verify weighted score calculations use correct category weights
Check that all subcategories are included in calculations
Conclusion
This lab provided hands-on experience implementing a Security Awareness Maturity Model (SAMM) assessment framework. You learned to:

Structure a maturity assessment system with configurable categories and levels
Process survey data to calculate organizational security awareness maturity
Apply statistical analysis to identify trends and patterns in security awareness
Generate actionable recommendations based on assessment results
Create comprehensive reports for stakeholders
The SAMM framework is valuable for organizations to measure and improve their security awareness programs systematically. By understanding current maturity levels and following data-driven recommendations, organizations can enhance their security posture through improved awareness and culture.

Key takeaways:

Maturity models provide structured approaches to capability assessment
Data-driven analysis reveals insights not visible through subjective evaluation
Weighted scoring ensures important categories receive appropriate emphasis
Continuous measurement enables tracking progress over time
Actionable recommendations drive meaningful improvement initiatives
Apply these concepts to assess and improve security awareness in real-world organizational contexts.
